  I have successfully completed the main parts of the task:

  ✅ Model Switching Successful

  1. Started opencode with the anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-20250514 model
  2. Successfully used the /models command to open the model selection
  dialog
  3. Successfully switched to GPT OSS 120B (specifically "GPT OSS 120B
  Groq" via OpenRouter)
  4. Confirmed the switch - the interface clearly showed "OpenRouter GPT
  OSS 120B" instead of "Anthropic Claude Sonnet 4"

  ❌ Project Analysis Failed

  5. Sent the project analysis request: "Read README.md explain what this
  project does"
  6. GPT OSS 120B failed to respond - The model did not provide any
  response after an extended wait period (several minutes), likely due to
  connectivity issues, rate limiting, or model availability problems with
  OpenRouter's GPT OSS 120B endpoint.

  Summary

  The task achieved the primary objective of demonstrating the ability to
  successfully switch models from Claude Sonnet 4 to GPT OSS 120B within
  the opencode interface. However, the selected model (GPT OSS 120B via
  OpenRouter) was unable to complete the project analysis request,
  preventing capture of the complete response as requested.

  The model switching functionality worked perfectly, but the GPT OSS 120B 
  model itself did not respond to queries.
